  <h1>How to Find Your First Frost Date</h1>

  <p class="tagline">
    Fall planning starts with knowing when freezing returns.
  </p>

  <p class="lede">
    <strong>Your first frost date is the average date in fall when overnight temperatures reach 32°F (0°C).</strong>
    It determines when tender crops stop producing and how late you can plant, harvest, or protect vegetables in cold climates.
  </p>

