<section class="card">
  <h2>What “First Frost Date” Means</h2>

  <p>
    Your <strong>average first frost date</strong> is a historical average, not a prediction.
    It marks when freezing nights become likely again in fall.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Some years frost arrives earlier.</li>
    <li>Some years it arrives later.</li>
    <li>Microclimates can shift your real timing by several days.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

